00:02:50.514 --> 00:02:55.072
And if you look over this
interval, it looks like,

00:02:55.072 --> 00:02:57.109
over that interval, over
that closed interval,

00:02:57.109 --> 00:02:59.967
our function just really
looks like a line.

00:02:59.967 --> 00:03:02.729
And so it is both continuous
and differentiable

00:03:02.729 --> 00:03:04.012
over that interval,

00:03:04.012 --> 00:03:05.944
and it makes sense that the
mean value theorem applies.

00:03:05.944 --> 00:03:09.189
Actually, every c on this interval is the

00:03:09.189 --> 00:03:11.317
derivative, is the
instantaneous rate of change

00:03:11.317 --> 00:03:12.773
equal to the average rate of change

00:03:12.773 --> 00:03:15.233
because it looks linear
over this interval.

00:03:15.233 --> 00:03:18.644
So the mean value theorem
definitely applies over there.

