The average rate of change
between the endpoints

00:04:08.293 --> 00:04:10.270
of our interval,

00:04:10.270 --> 00:04:12.820
or if we want to think about
the slope of the secant line,

00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:14.345
that's that right over there,

00:04:14.345 --> 00:04:17.711
and over the interval,
we don't see any point

00:04:17.711 --> 00:04:19.257
where the instantaneous rate of change,

00:04:19.257 --> 00:04:20.827
where the slope of the tangent line

00:04:20.827 --> 00:04:23.800
is equal to the slope of the secant line

00:04:23.800 --> 00:04:27.015
between the endpoints of our interval.

00:04:27.015 --> 00:04:30.215
So once again, mean value
theorem would not apply.

00:04:30.215 --> 00:04:33.430
Now, what about from
negative three to two?

00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:34.486
I'll do this in orange.

00:04:34.486 --> 00:04:38.569
So from negative three,
right over there, to two.

00:04:40.297 --> 00:04:41.972
Well, if we look at the open interval

00:04:41.972 --> 00:04:43.828
from negative three to two,

00:04:43.828 --> 00:04:45.262
